description:
## Severity
Major
## Dimension
security
## Location
src/plugins/manager.rs:575-608, src/plugins/git.rs:101-114
## Violation
The PluginSource::Path branch correctly rejects path-traversal in the *plugin* root via canonicalize and starts_with, but the moment the path passes that gate it is handed to copy_dir_recursive, which walks raw `fs::read_dir` entries and follows symlinks transparently (a symlink inside the plugin pointing at /home/user/.ssh/ would be copied byte-for-byte into the destination). Quoted lines:

    if !canonical.starts_with(&canonical_marketplace) {
        return Err(PluginError::IoError(format!(
            "Plugin path traversal detected: ...",
        )));
    }
    canonical
    ...
    // src/plugins/git.rs
    for entry in std::fs::read_dir(src)? {
        let entry = entry?;
        let src_path = entry.path();
        let dst_path = dst.join(entry.file_name());
        if src_path.is_dir() {
            copy_dir_recursive(&src_path, &dst_path)?;
        } else {
            std::fs::copy(&src_path, &dst_path)?;
        }
    }

`std::path::Path::is_dir()` follows symlinks, and `std::fs::copy` follows symlinks at the source — so a marketplace can ship a symlink that during install reads any user-readable file and stashes it inside .openclaudia/plugins/, where it then becomes referenced by InstalledPlugins.install_path with `install_path: dest.to_string_lossy()` and exposed via plugin loading.
## Mandated refactor
Switch copy_dir_recursive to use `symlink_metadata()` / `fs::metadata()` with `follow_symlinks=false`, refuse to copy any non-regular-file / non-directory entry, and refuse to copy entries whose canonicalised path escapes `src`. Add a strict allowlist of extensions (.md, .json, .yaml, .toml, .txt, executables only if explicitly allowed) so that compiled binaries cannot be smuggled in. Reject symlinks outright unless a future "trusted-marketplace" policy axis explicitly enables them.
